    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Pinpoint Tests - Reversing Lamps</title>
        <para>
            <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test T: The Reversing Lamps Are Inoperative</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Under normal operation, when the vehicle is in REVERSE, the transmission control module (TCM) provides a
            ground to the reversing lamp relay coil through circuit 1789 (VT/WH). Voltage is supplied to the reversing
            lamp relay coil through circuit 296 (WH/VT). Battery voltage is supplied from the power distribution center
            (PDC) fuse 16 (15A) to the reversing lamp relay switch through circuit 175 (BK/YE). When the relay is
            energized, voltage is sent to the reversing lamps through circuit 140 (BK/PK). The reversing lamps are
            grounded through circuit 57 (BK).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>An open in circuit 57 (BK), 140 (BK/PK), 175 (BK/YE), 296 (WH/VT) or 1789 (VT/WH)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Fuse</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Transmission control module (TCM)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Reversing lamp relay</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <table id="t1701080" tblwidth="pg-wide">
            <title>PINPOINT TEST T: THE REVERSING LAMPS ARE INOPERATIVE</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Test Step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">T1 CHECK THE VOLTAGE TO THE REVERSING LAMP RELAY COIL</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                        Reversing Lamp Relay.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the voltage between ground and reversing lamp relay pin 86, circuit
                                        296 (WH/VT).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0020210.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>GO to T2.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 296 (WH/VT) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">T2 CHECK THE TCM REVERSING LAMP RELAY OUTPUT</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Apply the parking brake.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Place the vehicle in REVERSE.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the voltage between reversing lamp relay pin 86, circuit 296 (WH/VT)
                                        and pin 87, circuit 1789 (VT/WH).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0024007.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>GO to T4.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>GO to T3.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">T3 CHECK CIRCUIT 1789 (VT/WH) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                        TCM C168.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the resistance between ground and reversing lamp relay pin 87, circuit
                                        1789 (VT/WH).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0020416.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>INSTALL a new TCM. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 1789 (VT/WH) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">T4 CHECK THE VOLTAGE TO THE REVERSING LAMP RELAY SWITCH</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the voltage between ground and reversing lamp relay pin 30, circuit
                                        175 (BK/YE).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <graphic filename="../fign00/n0020014.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>CARRY OUT the reversing lamp relay component test. Refer to the Wiring Diagrams for
                                component testing. If OK, GO to T5.
                            </para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>VERIFY the power distribution center (PDC) fuse 16 (15A) is OK. If OK, REPAIR circuit
                                175 (BK/YE) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">T5 CHECK CIRCUIT 140 (BK/PK) FOR AN OPEN</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>Inoperative Reversing Lamp.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the resistance between the inoperative reversing lamp, circuit 140
                                        (BK/PK) and reversing lamp relay pin 87, circuit 140 (BK/PK).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 57 (BK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 140 (BK/PK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>
            <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test U: An Individual Reversing Lamp Is Inoperative</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Under normal operation, when the relay is energized, voltage is sent to the reversing lamps through
            circuit 140 (BK/PK). The reversing lamps are grounded through circuit 57 (BK).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>An open in circuit 57 (BK) or 140 (BK/PK)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Bulb/lamp</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <table id="t1701079" tblwidth="pg-wide">
            <title>PINPOINT TEST U: AN INDIVIDUAL REVERSING LAMP IS INOPERATIVE</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Test Step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">U1 CHECK THE VOLTAGE TO THE INOPERATIVE REVERSING LAMP</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                        Inoperative Reversing Lamp.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in ON position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Apply the parking brake.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Place the vehicle in REVERSE.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the voltage between ground and the inoperative reversing lamp, circuit
                                        140 (BK/PK).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the voltage greater than 10 volts?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>GO to U2.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 140 (BK/PK). TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">U2 CHECK GROUND TO THE INOPERATIVE REVERSING LAMP</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>Key in OFF position.</para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the resistance between ground and the inoperative reversing lamp
                                        ground circuit.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the resistance less than 5 ohms?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>INSPECT the bulb for an open. If OK, INSTALL a new lamp. TEST the system for normal
                                operation.
                            </para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 57 (BK) for an open. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>
            <emph type="italic">Pinpoint Test V: The Reversing Lamps Are ON Continuously</emph>
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Normal Operation</emph>
        </para>
        <para>Under normal operation, when the vehicle is in REVERSE, the transmission control module (TCM) provides a
            ground to the reversing lamp relay coil through circuit 1789 (VT/WH). When the relay is energized, voltage
            is sent to the reversing lamps through circuit 140 (BK/PK).
        </para>
        <para>
            <emph type="bold">Possible Causes</emph>
        </para>
        <randlist type="bullet">
            <item>
                <para>A short to ground in circuit 1789 (VT/WH)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>A short to voltage in circuit 140 (BK/PK)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Transmission control module (TCM)</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Reversing lamp relay</para>
            </item>
        </randlist>
        <table id="t1701081" tblwidth="pg-wide">
            <title>PINPOINT TEST V: THE REVERSING LAMPS ARE ON CONTINUOUSLY</title>
            <tgroup cols="2">
                <colspec colname="col1" colwidth="1.14*"/>
                <colspec colname="col2" colwidth="0.86*"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Test Step</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry align="center">
                            <para>Result / Action to Take</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">V1 CHECK THE FOG LAMP RELAY</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>Reversing Lamp Relay.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Observe the reversing lamps.</para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Do the reversing lamps continue to illuminate?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 140 (BK/PK) for a short to voltage. TEST the system for normal
                                operation.
                            </para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>CARRY OUT the reversing lamp relay component test. Refer to the Wiring Diagrams for
                                component testing. If OK, GO to V2.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">V2 CHECK CIRCUIT 1789 (VT/WH) FOR A SHORT TO GROUND</emph>
                            </para>
                            <randlist type="bullet">
                                <item>
                                    <para>
                                        <emph type="bold">Disconnect:</emph>
                                        TCM C168.
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>Measure the resistance between ground and the reversing lamp relay pin 87,
                                        circuit 1789 (VT/WH).
                                    </para>
                                </item>
                            </randlist>
                            <graphic filename="../figa00/a0020416.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="232px"
                                     scalefitheight="152px"/>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Is the resistance greater than 10,000 ohms?</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">Yes</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>INSTALL a new TCM. TEST the system for normal operation.</para>
                            <para></para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">No</emph>
                            </para>
                            <para>REPAIR circuit 1789 (VT/WH) for a short to ground. TEST the system for normal
                                operation.
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
    </svcsubproc>
